scripts.text:
You stand outside a pair of imposing stone doors. A large series of cogs and gears are carved in their surfaces... though from a distance they look more like an empty-eyed skull to you. 

The doors hang ajar, and within you see rows of flickering torches and an indistinct figure brooding on a shadowy throne...

Westwards - The Throne Room
Southwards - The Storyteller's Market
Northwards - Kin Chambers
Eastwards - Delvings (restricted)
The shop is dark and dusty.

events.flavourText: You step into the shadowy halls of Aenen. Your footsteps echo from the tall vaulted ceilings and sturdy stone walls, many of which have been carven with strange mechanical looking reliefs. Here and there tar torches crackle and flicker, and in many places strange luminous globes on the ceiling provide light. Despite the gloom, the air smells surprisingly fresh and wholesome.

Gnomes can be seen all around, hurrying here and there in small groups, many carrying metallic objects that you do not recognise. A quiet buzz of movement and conversation fills the passages. You draw some curious glances but nobody approaches you.

scripts.text:
The passage ends abruptly in a rough hewn wall. 

Work on this thoroughfare does not seem to be complete.
